1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:09,679
Hi, my name's Pat and this is episode 11 of the 100K build challenge where I'm trying to see if I can make $100,000 using only AI tools.

2
00:00:09,679 --> 00:00:10,880
Quick update for you guys.

3
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:16,320
My app has now made over $2,500 and I think I might be on to something.

4
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:21,600
And I also think it might be because of one tough decision I made when starting this project.

5
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,840
And that's what I'm going to be sharing with you today.

6
00:00:23,840 --> 00:00:26,480
But before we get into that, let me remind you of the rules.

7
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:28,880
Rule one is that I can only use AI tools.

8
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:32,160
Rule two is I must document everything right here on this channel.

9
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:36,399
And rule three is that I cannot give up until I make $100,000.

10
00:00:36,399 --> 00:00:46,640
So without further ado, let's dive into episode 11 where I'm going to be sharing with you the dirty little secret I learned the hard way about what it might actually take to build a successful

11
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:48,640
product online.

12
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:53,760
Okay, so this story starts a few weeks ago when I was trying to figure out pricing for moat.

13
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:55,440
How am I going to price this tool?

14
00:00:55,440 --> 00:01:00,399
$5 a month, $10 a month, $30 a month, $10,000 a month.

15
00:01:00,399 --> 00:01:02,320
I honestly had no idea.

16
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:05,280
So, I did what any smart entrepreneur would do.

17
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:07,760
I decided to look at the data.

18
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:13,760
And as you guys might remember, my very first app from the challenge all the way back to episode 1,

19
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:16,400
well, that was the AI thumbnails generator.

20
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:20,240
And man, it just gives me PTSD bringing up these dashboards.

21
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:24,479
But what I wanted to know was what was my conversion rate?

22
00:01:24,479 --> 00:01:25,920
Well, let's dive in.

23
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:32,159
For people that visited the site and then clicked just to the signup page, that was only 2%.

24
00:01:32,159 --> 00:01:33,200
Which is quite bad.

25
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:39,520
But then actually, people that subscribed and paid, well, that was 0.1%.

26
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:40,960
Not 1%.

27
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:43,600
But onetenth of 1%.

28
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,520
0.1%.

29
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:46,560
Ouch.

30
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:48,320
That is not good.

31
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:52,560
And to make matters worse, it wasn't like the AI thumbnail generator was expensive.

32
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,000
It was $9 a month.

33
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,920
So, what do I do now?

34
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,439
Do I price it even lower?

35
00:01:57,439 --> 00:01:58,640
Do I price it higher?

36
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,159
Do I do yearly subscriptions?

37
00:02:00,159 --> 00:02:01,840
I did not have an answer for this.

38
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:04,799
And honestly, this was really demotivating.

39
00:02:04,799 --> 00:02:08,319
But everything changed when I got on a call with this guy named Devon.

40
00:02:08,319 --> 00:02:11,200
He's built a cool business that makes over $20,000 a month.

41
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:14,480
And I was interviewing him for the main Starter Story YouTube channel.

42
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:20,480
And over and over, he kept talking about this one thing, Lifetime Deals.

43
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,599
And immediately that got the juices flowing for me.

44
00:02:23,599 --> 00:02:29,040
What if I didn't charge a subscription at all and I did a one-time payment lifetime deal?

45
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:30,879
Would that solve all my problems?

46
00:02:30,879 --> 00:02:34,239
I started looking into this and honestly, I got mixed results.

47
00:02:34,239 --> 00:02:40,480
Some people say they regretted doing lifetime deals while others said it changed their business and it was the best decision they ever made.

48
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:46,239
There are certainly pros and cons to a strategy like this and honestly, I was a bit skeptical.

49
00:02:46,239 --> 00:02:48,239
Here were my main hesitations.

50
00:02:48,239 --> 00:02:57,920
Number one is that because my product uses LLM APIs which cost money, what would happen if a customer costs more than I actually make from them in terms of revenue.

51
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:04,720
My second hesitation was if I make all the revenue upfront from then I will lose all future revenue that I can make from that customer as well.

52
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:07,519
And my third hesitation was regarding support.

53
00:03:07,519 --> 00:03:09,519
As you guys know, I'm a one-man show.

54
00:03:09,519 --> 00:03:15,040
So what if these customers take away all my time from me and bombard me with support and questions?

55
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,879
I wasn't sure if this was the right move.

56
00:03:16,879 --> 00:03:18,720
and I had a lot of thinking to do.

57
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:22,239
So, I went on a long walk with Bernie and I weighed my options.

58
00:03:22,239 --> 00:03:25,840
And by the time I got home from my walk, I said, "Screw it.

59
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,680
What's the worst thing that could happen?

60
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:30,239
Let's give this one a try."

61
00:03:30,239 --> 00:03:31,440
So, that's what I did.

62
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:34,480
I priced my app at $19 for lifetime access.

63
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:37,440
And within hours, people started buying.

64
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:42,400
The conversion rate compared to the AI Thumbnails maker was even more staggering.

65
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,760
It skyrocketed.

66
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:47,440
It was seven times higher than it was in the Thumbnails app.

67
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:50,400
That's like over a thousand% increase.

68
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:55,680
I was super excited about that, but I was still unsure how it would impact the business.

69
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,040
Would it still be profitable?

70
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,640
Would I be drowning in support?

71
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:01,040
Am I shooting myself in the foot by doing this?

72
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:07,519
Well, over the next few days, I learned and realized a few things that changed my mind on this whole lifetime deal thing.

73
00:04:07,519 --> 00:04:13,120
So, in terms of time, my big hesitation was, how will adding a lifetime deal impact my customer support?

74
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:17,280
Can I afford to spend 20 hours supporting one customer who paid $19?

75
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:20,880
Well, then I realized early on that's the wrong way to think.

76
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:25,199
If one person buys your product and actually uses it, that's gold.

77
00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:26,960
You're not losing 20 hours.

78
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:34,560
You're investing 20 hours into learning what customers need, fixing their problems, and getting your product closer to product market fit.

79
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:38,000
In fact, the scarier situation is the opposite.

80
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:43,360
someone pays you or never pays you at all, never uses the tool and quietly leaves.

81
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:46,320
That means no feedback, no retention and no growth.

82
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:52,800
At the beginning, you should want people who use the product so much that they need your time and support and ask you questions.

83
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,120
The second hesitation was around costs.

84
00:04:55,120 --> 00:05:00,800
What if a customer ends up costing me more in LLM API usage than the $19 I made from them?

85
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:06,720
Well, the truth is that very few customers will ever use it forever at 100% capacity.

86
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:11,440
Most lifetime buyers just want to tinker, try the tool, or use it for a single project.

87
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:15,680
And over time, usage naturally drops off just like with any product in the world.

88
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:21,440
Devon, the guy I talked to, he said that only a tiny fraction of his lifetime customers are still active.

89
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,479
That's not a failure.

90
00:05:22,479 --> 00:05:24,160
That's just how lifetime deals work.

91
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:29,199
Think of it as a one-mon subscription paid upfront with some people sticking around longer.

92
00:05:29,199 --> 00:05:31,360
The economics usually balance out.

93
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:34,240
The third hesitation I had was around revenue losses.

94
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:39,280
If I take lifetime payment upfront, I'll lose all future subscription revenue from that customer.

95
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:42,880
Well, the truth is I realized that I wasn't locking myself into lifetime forever.

96
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:46,400
The priority right now is not in maximizing LTV.

97
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:51,199
It's about getting momentum with this product, getting users feedback, a little bit of cash,

98
00:05:51,199 --> 00:05:52,240
and social proof.

99
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:55,600
Later, I can switch to subscriptions, raise prices, and change the model.

100
00:05:55,600 --> 00:06:03,039
Sure, those lifetime buyers will get grandfathered in because without them, I probably wouldn't have been able to get this product off the ground in the first place.

101
00:06:03,039 --> 00:06:05,520
Right now, it's not about the sales.

102
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,039
Customers are giving me feedback.

103
00:06:07,039 --> 00:06:11,199
They're telling me what they like, what's broken, and what features they want next.

104
00:06:11,199 --> 00:06:19,360
That feedback is worth way more than the few thousand dollars I've made so far with the project because I know I'm building something for the long run.

105
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:23,600
Something that will make tens or hundreds of thousands of dollars per month eventually.

106
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:26,080
And I want to get there by building a great product.

107
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:29,840
And I will not get there if I don't get feedback from actual customers.

108
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:35,919
So, with all of this, I realized that a lifetime deal for me right now is actually the move.

109
00:06:35,919 --> 00:06:36,800
I tried it.

110
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,680
It's working.

111
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,440
So, I'm going to keep doing that.

112
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,560
And here's my plan.

113
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:43,280
I started with lifetime deals to validate and get momentum.

114
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:48,400
And as I add more features, I will slowly raise that lifetime price over time.

115
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:53,440
And then eventually, when it feels right, I will transition the product to subscriptions.

116
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:59,840
But right now, $19 is a no-brainer buy, especially considering other products cost more than $19 a month.

117
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:04,639
And with Moat, you get a database of proven social media templates that you can use right now.

118
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:06,880
That makes that $19 price a no-brainer.

119
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:12,479
As I continue to get feedback and at the end of the day, I realized just because other people are doing subscriptions,

120
00:07:12,479 --> 00:07:15,120
that doesn't mean that I have to do it.

121
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:21,280
I dropped my ego and realized that lots of other businesses do this lifetime thing, so there must be a reason for it.

122
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:22,400
That's why I tried it.

123
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,720
It worked and I'm going to keep doing that right now.

124
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:30,080
So, if you're building anything or planning on launching anything soon, consider starting with a lifetime deal.

125
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:35,360
Get a few people to pay you something and use that momentum to keep building and build something great.

126
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:38,160
This has been episode 11 of the 100K build challenge.

127
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:42,080
Thank you guys for watching and let me know in the comments what you think about lifetime deals.

128
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,039
Would you buy one?

129
00:07:43,039 --> 00:07:45,840
I'll see you in the next one.
